    {
      "id": "895e0e3a18f8e074647dab4ffd57fbaa4041fd9d",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 131,
        "name": "Jian Yu",
        "email": "yujian@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "yujian"
      },
      "date": "2016-10-22 09:50:26.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> can you please explain who'll be using all this?\n\nHi Alex,\n\nHongchao created this patch to be used by http://review.whamcloud.com/7200.\n\nIf this patch passed review, the following changes will be added to patch #7200:\n\n --- a/lustre/tests/test-framework.sh\n +++ b/lustre/tests/test-framework.sh\n @@ -1451,7 +1451,9 @@ set_dev_readonly() {\n            ! dm_flakey_supported $facet; then\n                 do_facet $facet $LCTL --device ${!svc} readonly\n         else\n +               do_facet $facet $LCTL --device ${!svc} freeze\n                 dm_set_dev_readonly $facet\n +               do_facet $facet $LCTL --device ${!svc} unfreeze\n         fi\n  }",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "f931592cdc9e6a5372d808b47fa1ac97e0745a19",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 131,
        "name": "Jian Yu",
        "email": "yujian@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "yujian"
      },
      "date": "2016-10-22 09:54:56.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nHi Hongchao,\n\nI verified the above changes and found it resolved the issue in LU-8729. The replay-single and conf-sanity tests passed. However, replay-dual test 21b failed, which passed before:\n https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sessions/be1f3e8c-97d2-11e6-9626-5254006e85c2\n https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sessions/1afd37ac-97f2-11e6-9251-5254006e85c2",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "79e64a3d501e0d2cffaee65f27bd1c8f57882b06",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 131,
        "name": "Jian Yu",
        "email": "yujian@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "yujian"
      },
      "date": "2016-10-22 10:00:32.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nOn early patch set of http://review.whamcloud.com/7200 , replay-dual test 21b also failed. At that time, Alex suggested making the following changes to resolve the failure:\n\n@@ -1383,7 +1383,7 @@ dm_set_dev_table() {\n        *) error \"invalid target type $target_type\" ;;\n        esac\n \n-       do_facet $facet \"$DMSETUP suspend $dm_dev\" ||\n+       do_facet $facet \"$DMSETUP suspend --nolockfs --noflush $dm_dev\" ||\n                error \"failed to suspend $dm_dev\"\n        do_facet $facet \"$DMSETUP load $dm_dev --table \\\\\\\"$table\\\\\\\"\" ||\n                error \"failed to load $target_type table into $dm_dev\"\n\nAfter applying the above changes, replay-dual test 21b passed.\n\nHowever, with this freeze/unfreeze patch, replay-dual test 21b failed again.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "09b65d4fbe0464859261ea159de6078a355e6f49",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2016-10-24 12:11:10.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI wonder why a regular sync(1) is not enough",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "97c04e89e3c2d7f8b238802c4ba4eae3cf8e170e",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 131,
        "name": "Jian Yu",
        "email": "yujian@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "yujian"
      },
      "date": "2016-10-25 03:09:15.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nHi Hongchao,\n\nCould you please take a look at the above comments? Thank you.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "a3d83edc4dc77bba251ccb3369b1b505898a85e0",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 144,
        "name": "Hongchao Zhang",
        "email": "hongchao@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "Hongchao.zhang"
      },
      "date": "2016-10-25 10:48:29.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nHi Bzzz,\n\nThe reason to use \"freeze\" if the normal sync can't guarantee all writes are committed to disk,\nthe ticket LU-7428 was created to track such problem. but the reason why the writes are missing is unknown,\nand it could be a result of bad interactions with LVM and VM virtual block devices.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "cdc1cc76a25cd6d3ef193ea0ea1875a7e4286575",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2016-10-25 12:54:50.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI'm a bit concerned that we don't understand why sync doesn't work and just add a new code ..",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
